The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) on Friday announced the names of 36 probables for the 14-day physical conditioning-cum-mental toughness camp to be held at the Eden from Sunday. Former South African trainer Adrian Le Roux will supervise the physical conditioning camp.            
	The squad: Sourav Ganguly, Laxmi Ratan Shukla, Manoj Tiwary, Anustup Majumdar, Arindam Das, Amitava Chakraborty, Rohan Banerjee, Soham Ghosh, Avik Mallick, Mohammed Ziauddin, Partha Sarathi Bhattacharjee, Abhishek Banerjee, Prinan Dutta, Kamal Hassan Mondal, Safi Ahmed, Debabrata Das, Dibendyu Chakraborty, Charanjit Singh, Subhradip Ganguly, Aranyadeb Sarkar, Wriddhiman Saha, Sreevats Goswami, Iresh Saxena, Rajkumar Paul, Sourasish Lahiri, Ritam Kundu, Priyankar Mukherjee, Ranadeb Bose, Shib Shankar Paul, Ashok Dinda, Sourav Sarkar, Avik Chowdhury, Arindam Ghosh, Sougata Dutta, Kamalesh Patel, Ambarish Mitra                
	 Forty-two teams, including a ladies team, from all parts of the country participated in the 3rd All India Bridge tournament that started at the Hindusthan Club on Friday. The meet has a total prize money of Rs 3.20 lakh and the finals will be held on Sunday.                       
	 Laxmipath Singhania beat Mahadevi Birla Sishu Vihar in the girls team championship of the Patterson Memorial Inter School Table Tennis championship at the Khudiram Anushilan Kendra on Friday.                      
	 The 32nd All Bengal Promothonath-Nanigopal Memorial (Open) Water Polo meet will start on Saturday. Twelve state teams are scheduled to participate in the two-day format knockout tournament.                
	BRIDGE: 3rd All India meet at the Hindusthan Club from 11am      
	FOOTBALL: CFL Premier Division match  United SC vs CPT at Barasat 3.30pm      
	POLO: All Bengal Promothonath-Nanigopal Memorial (Open) meet from 8am      
	TABLE TENNIS: Patterson Memorial Inter School meet from 10am                                                                                                                                                                     
